  "yogaDescHeadNeck": "Gentle seated stretches releasing neck and shoulder tension.",
  "yogaDescGentleChair": "Make sure the chair is stable by placing it against a wall. Beginner’s level of Chair yoga is suitable for most people. Yoga should be practised with an empty or relatively empty stomach, or at least 2 hours after a meal.",
  "yogaDescMorningMobility": "A light morning routine focusing on joint mobility, breathing, and supported strength work.",
  "yogaDescWarriorSeries": "A confidence-building sequence exploring Warrior I, II, and supporting transitions.",
  "yogaDescHathaFundamentals": "A classic mat-based Hatha sequence focusing on alignment, breath, and full-body engagement. Ideal for practitioners ready to move beyond chair support.",
  "yogaDescCoreStrength": "A short but powerful session focusing on Plank, Eight-Point Pose, and controlled transitions. Boosts core strength and shoulder stability.",
  "yogaDescBackbendFlow": "A spine-strengthening sequence moving from Eight-Point Pose into Baby Cobra and Full Cobra. Builds confidence in backbending.",
  "yogaDescSunSalutationSession": "A dynamic mat-based flow designed to synchronise breath and movement. This session builds endurance and full-body strength through repeated Sun Salutation cycles.",
  "yogaDescExtendedFlow": "A deeper and longer Sun Salutation practice — ideal for experienced practitioners wanting a continuous challenge with breath-led movement.",
  "yogaDescStraightArms": "Arm rotations to warm up shoulders and upper back.",
  "yogaDescBentArms": "Shoulder mobility exercise with bent elbows.",
  "yogaDescShouldersLateral": "Side-body stretch improving flexibility.",
  "yogaDescShouldersTorsoTwist": "A gentle detoxifying twist.",
  "yogaDescLegRaiseBent": "Strengthen legs and activate core.",
  "yogaDescLegRaiseStraight": "Straight-leg lift for advanced strength.",
  "yogaDescGoddessTwist": "Wide-leg seated pose for mobility.",
  "yogaDescGoddessStrength": "Strengthening variation of seated Goddess.",
  "yogaDescBackChestStretch": "L-shape stretch improving upper-body flexibility.",
  "yogaDescStandingCrunch": "Dynamic core-strengthening movement.",
  "yogaDescWarrior3Supported": "Balance and strength with chair support.",
  "yogaDescWarrior1Supported": "Beginner-friendly Warrior stance.",
  "yogaDescWarrior2Supported": "Side-facing warrior for hip opening.",
  "yogaDescTriangleSupported": "Deep side-body extension.",
  "yogaDescReverseWarrior2": "Back-arching warrior stretch.",
  "yogaDescSideAngleSupported": "Strengthens legs and opens ribs.",
  "yogaDescGentleBreathing": "Full-body relaxation and calm breathing.",
  "yogaDescDownwardDog": "A foundational inverted V pose that stretches the full body.",
  "yogaDescPlank": "Full-body strength builder engaging core, arms, and legs.",
  "yogaDescEightPoint": "Strength-building pose lowering chest, chin, knees and toes.",
  "yogaDescBabyCobra": "Gentle backbend strengthening upper back and spine.",
  "yogaDescFullCobra": "A stronger chest-opening backbend engaging the whole body.",
  "yogaDescSunSalutation": "A dynamic sequence linking breath and movement. Builds strength, heat, coordination, and stamina.",
  "yogaInstHeadNeck": "Tilt head up/down for 5–10 breaths each. Turn head right/left 3 rounds. Drop ear to shoulder with light hand support.",
  "yogaInstStraightArms": "Make fists, rotate straight arms 10 times forward and 10 times backward.",
  "yogaInstBentArms": "Touch elbows in front, circle up behind head and back down. 10 rounds each direction.",
  "yogaInstShouldersLateral": "Drop right hand to chair, lift left arm overhead. Hold 5–10 breaths. Switch sides.",
  "yogaInstShouldersTorsoTwist": "Lift arms, rotate torso right, hold chair for support. Hold 5–10 breaths each side.",
  "yogaInstLegRaiseBent": "Lift bent leg with back straight. Hold, lower with control. Switch legs.",
  "yogaInstLegRaiseStraight": "Lift straightened leg, hold as long as possible. Release and switch legs.",
  "yogaInstGoddessTwist": "Open knees wide, stretch torso to side. Hold 5–10 breaths, switch side.",
  "yogaInstGoddessStrength": "Lift thighs off chair while in Goddess stance. Hold 5–10 breaths. Repeat.",
  "yogaInstBackChestStretch": "Hold chair, hinge into L-shape, keep back flat. Hold 5–10 breaths.",
  "yogaInstStandingCrunch": "From L-shape, extend leg back on inhale, crunch knee forward on exhale. Repeat.",
  "yogaInstWarrior3": "Lift hand off chair, hold balance. Switch legs and repeat.",
  "yogaInstWarrior1": "Step back, bend front knee, raise arms. Hold 5–10 breaths.",
  "yogaInstWarrior2": "Turn toes outward, stretch arms, look forward. Hold.",
  "yogaInstTriangle": "Straighten front leg, lower hand to ankle or block, reach upward.",
  "yogaInstReverseWarrior": "Sweep top arm overhead while leaning back. Hold.",
  "yogaInstSideAngle": "Lower hand inside foot, stretch upper arm diagonally overhead.",
  "yogaInstGentleBreathing": "Relax shoulders, place hands on lap, breathe slowly through the nose.",
  "yogaInstDownwardDog": "Place hands shoulder-width apart, feet hip-width apart. Lift hips high, press chest towards thighs. Hold 5–10 breaths.",
  "yogaInstPlank": "Stack shoulders over wrists, engage core, lengthen from head to heels. Hold 5–10 breaths.",
  "yogaInstEightPoint": "From tabletop, lower chest and chin to mat while hips stay lifted. Hold 5–10 breaths.",
  "yogaInstBabyCobra": "From prone, press chest up lightly, keep elbows close and shoulders away from ears. Hold 5–10 breaths.",
  "yogaInstFullCobra": "Straighten elbows, lift chest higher without scrunching shoulders. Hold 5–10 breaths.",
  "yogaInstGentleBreathingIntermediate": "Place hands on belly or lap, relax shoulders, breathe through the nose slowly and naturally.",
  "yogaInstSunSalutation": "This flowing sequence repeats continuously — one breath per movement.\n 1. Inhale — Downward Dog\n Lift hips high, lengthen spine.\n 2. Exhale — Plank\n Shift forward into strong plank position.\n 3. Inhale — Knees-Chest-Chin (Eight-Point Pose)\n Lower down with control, hips lifted.\n 4. Exhale — Baby Cobra\n Lift chest gently, elbows close.\n 5. Inhale — Full Cobra\n Straighten arms slightly, open chest.\n 6. Exhale — Return to Downward Dog\n Press back into inverted V-shape.\n Repeat for 5–10 rounds or to your ability level.",
  "yogaGentleBreathingAdvanced": "Breathe softly through the nose, lengthening exhales. Allow the entire body to settle and cool down.",
